# yfitops V2 — environment template.
# Copy to deploy/.env (gitignored) and fill in. Most vars map to a field read
# by server/internal/config/config.go; the VITE_* block is read by the dev
# launcher for the browser frontends. Defaults below are dev-safe; the server
# boots with all of them even if .env is absent.
#
#   cp deploy/.env.example deploy/.env
#
# Two consumers read deploy/.env:
#   - docker compose (deploy/docker-compose.yml) for production-ish runs
#   - scripts/dev-up.sh for the one-command local browser playtest
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# SECURITY — change these before any non-local deployment.
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Gates the admin / Control Room AND the trusted Stage screen (design_doc §9).
# Both clients must present this secret. CHANGE IT — default is a placeholder.
ADMIN_SECRET=changeme-admin

# HMAC key for the anti-cheat nonce gate (§4D). Any long random string.
YFI_NONCE_SECRET=dev-nonce-secret

# HMAC key signing the rotating QR join tokens (§3.1). Any long random string.
YFI_JOIN_SECRET=dev-join-secret

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# SPOTIFY — REQUIRED for real audio playback.
# Setup (one-time, ~5 min):
#   1. https://developer.spotify.com/dashboard -> "Create app".
#   2. Add a Redirect URI EXACTLY equal to SPOTIFY_REDIRECT_URI below
#      (byte-for-byte: 127.0.0.1 not localhost, http not https, no trailing /).
#      A mismatch fails with "INVALID_CLIENT: Invalid redirect URI".
#   3. Enable both "Web API" and "Web Playback SDK".
#   4. Copy the Client ID + Client Secret into the two vars below.
#   5. The stage browser must be logged into a Spotify PREMIUM account —
#      the Web Playback SDK only emits audio for Premium.
# Without these the server still runs, but the stage uses a mock player
# (demo mode, no audio).
#
# Token lifecycle: access tokens expire ~1h after issue regardless of activity.
# The backend refreshes them via the stored refresh token and serves a live one
# from GET /api/spotify/token, so audio survives a multi-hour game — no action
# needed here beyond the credentials.
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
SPOTIFY_CLIENT_ID=
SPOTIFY_CLIENT_SECRET=
SPOTIFY_REDIRECT_URI=http://127.0.0.1:8777/auth/spotify/callback

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# DATA LAYER — defaults point at the compose service names. Override only if
# running the server outside compose. If unreachable at boot, the server falls
# back to in-memory store + a seeded sample board (see cmd/gameserver/main.go).
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
YFI_REDIS_ADDR=redis:6379
YFI_POSTGRES_DSN=postgres://yfitops:yfitops@postgres:5432/yfitops?sslmode=disable

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# NETWORK / TLS — must match the published compose ports.
# 4433 is UDP (QUIC/HTTP3/WebTransport); 8777 is TCP (health/OAuth/cert-hash).
# Cert files default to /certs/*.pem inside the container; the server
# auto-generates a self-signed pair there on first boot if missing.
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
YFI_LISTEN_ADDR=:4433
YFI_HTTP_ADDR=:8777
YFI_CERT_FILE=/certs/cert.pem
YFI_KEY_FILE=/certs/key.pem

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# LYRICS / GAMEPLAY — optional tuning.
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# LRCLIB synced-lyrics source (§6). Public instance by default.
YFI_LRCLIB_URL=https://lrclib.net

# Skip-vote threshold percent of active users, 50-100 (§3.8).
YFI_SKIP_THRESHOLD=50

# Logical game session id used for persistence keys.
YFI_SESSION_ID=session

# Board dimensions (default 5x5 Jeopardy grid). Read by config.go.
YFI_BOARD_ROWS=5
YFI_BOARD_COLS=5

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# FRONTEND (Vite) — read by scripts/dev-up.sh, NOT by the Go server. These are
# normally derived automatically by the launcher (host 127.0.0.1 + the ports
# below) and only need overriding for a LAN/remote setup. VITE_STAGE_SECRET
# MUST equal ADMIN_SECRET — the Stage authenticates with it (hello + the
# Spotify token endpoint).
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# VITE_WT_URL=https://127.0.0.1:4433/wt        # WebTransport endpoint
# VITE_HTTP_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8777          # health / OAuth / cert-hash / token
# VITE_JOIN_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8780          # mobile buzzer URL encoded in the QR
# VITE_STAGE_SECRET=changeme-admin             # must match ADMIN_SECRET
